-- Finance Ministry Sells 182-Day Treasury Bills at 1.798% Yield, Traders Say
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-23T02:35:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/finance-ministry-sells-182-day-treasury-bills-at-1-798-yield-traders-say.html

          
          
             China’s finance ministry sold 20
billion yuan ($2.95 billion) of 182-day bills at an average
yield of 1.798 percent, according to traders at Industrial Bank
Co. and Industrial and Commercial Bank of China Ltd.  
 The average yield compared with the 1.772 percent yield in
secondary-market trading yesterday, according to rates compiled
by Chinabond, the nation’s biggest debt-clearing house. The
government last sold similar-maturity bills July 9 at 1.9256
percent.  
